The currency of Haiti is the Gourde. On 1 March 2018, the Government of Haiti announced that all commercial transactions would be undertaken in the Haitian Gourde.
Wherever possible, avoid using banks or withdrawing money at cash points (see Crime). Don’t change money on the street. You can exchange US Dollars cash or travellers’ cheques for local currency in large hotels.
There is a risk of credit card cloning and theft. It’s generally safer to use cash. Most credit cards can be used in major hotels, and in some shops and businesses in the large towns and cities.
